<H1>Global replace</H1>

<P>To replace every occurrence of a piece of text from the
cursor to the end of the file:</P>

<P><STRONG>1.</STRONG> Type <STRONG>M-R</STRONG>.</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   Replace []&lt;META&gt;:
</PRE>

<P><STRONG>2.</STRONG> Type in the text you want to replace and
press the META key.</P>

<P>You will then be prompted for the new text, with a
prompt like this:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   with []&lt;META&gt;:
</PRE>

<P><STRONG>3.</STRONG> Type in the new text and press the META key</P>

<P>All the occurrences of the old text will be replaced
by the new and the number of changes printed at the
bottom of your screen, for example:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   36 substitutions
</PRE>

